reviews.review_text: Lucky Us! Well, this sounds great!  Another fabulous post from you know who.  I'm uping the vocals a little with the equalizer.  A fine audience recording from 10/72 givin light of day for the world in 05/09 - Awesome!
thanks THANK YOU MR MILLER WOW!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Thanks from Milwaukee Thanks for this hometown show.  
I believe the patch source on this recording is from the same source as used on the other copy of this show on the archive, the "cotsman" master, but the patch source here sounds to be of a lower generation, to my ears much clearer.
Milwaukee-72 72, grate year. the dead were on it.this show is hot.thanks for this grate show, grate recording Charlie.it does'nt get any better than this!!!!!.
- Nothing wrong with this! Despite the cloudy sound, the show and the recording's depth and warmth make a great listen.
vintage high energy two hour first set (gorgeous Stella, sick Deal) and Dark Star...
this Dark Star is EPIC just give it a listen. well worth your time.
